   confined to the left column's own width like the pattern content above
   it. No explicit grid-row: it auto-places into a fresh row once row 1's
   column-1 cell is taken by .col-left, leaving column 2 of that row empty
   rather than pulling it in beside the sticky Progress card. */
:global(.card-congrats) {
  grid-column: 1;
}

.card {
